      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-brand-blue mt-0 mb-4">When Your Ductwork Needs Attention</h2>

      <p>You crank the AC and one room feels great while the next one over is still warm. Or maybe your energy bill jumped for no obvious reason. Nine times out of ten, that's a duct problem, not an equipment problem. HiLo Heating and Air handles <strong>HVAC duct repair</strong>, <strong>ductwork repair</strong>, and <strong>HVAC duct replacement</strong> for homes across Stanton, CA and the rest of Orange County — and it's usually a quicker, cheaper fix than people expect.</p>

      <h2>How Do You Know You Need Duct Repair?</h2>
      <p>Ducts don't fail all at once. It's gradual. A seam loosens, a section gets crushed in the attic, rodents chew through insulation, and slowly your system starts losing efficiency without anyone noticing right away. By the time you spot uneven temperatures or hear whistling sounds near the vents, there's usually a real issue back there.</p>
      <p>That's when <strong>HVAC duct repair</strong> makes sense — patching leaks, resealing joints, fixing crushed or disconnected sections before the problem spreads further through the system.</p>

      <h2>When Repair Isn't Enough</h2>
      <p>Sometimes the damage is too far gone. Ducts from older homes — especially anything original to the build — can be brittle, undersized, or just falling apart in places you can't even see without pulling back insulation. In those cases, <strong>ductwork repair</strong> alone won't cut it, and we'll be upfront about that instead of patching something that's going to fail again in six months.</p>
      <p><strong>HVAC duct replacement</strong> becomes the better call when ducts are too damaged, too old, or sized wrong for your current system. We'll walk you through exactly why, show you what we're seeing, and let you decide from there.</p>

      <h2>What HiLo Heating and Air Actually Does</h2>
      <p>Every job starts with an inspection — we check accessible ductwork, look for leaks with smoke or pressure testing where needed, and figure out whether we're looking at <strong>HVAC duct repair</strong> or something bigger. We don't push replacement just because it's the bigger job. If repair fixes it, we say so.</p>
      <p>When repair is the right call, we seal with proper mastic (not tape — tape always fails eventually), patch damaged sections, and reinsulate where needed. When <strong>HVAC duct replacement</strong> is the better option, we size everything correctly for your home and current HVAC equipment, then install ductwork that's actually built to last.</p>

      <h2>Why Get This Fixed Sooner Than Later</h2>
      <p>Leaky or damaged ducts waste a surprising amount of conditioned air — sometimes 20-30% before it even reaches your vents. That's money going straight into your attic or crawlspace. Beyond the cost, damaged ductwork can pull dust, allergens, and even pests into your air supply, which affects everyone breathing it.</p>
      <p>With HiLo Heating and Air, you get straight answers about whether you need <strong>ductwork repair</strong> or a full replacement, fair pricing either way, and a crew that actually explains what they found instead of just handing you a bill.</p>

      <h2>Schedule Your Inspection Today</h2>
      <p>Don't keep paying for air your house never actually gets. Contact HiLo Heating and Air to schedule a duct inspection, and we'll tell you honestly whether repair or replacement makes more sense for your home.</p>
